/*
 * Keep a single physical layout on the Corne peripherals.
 *
 * Since ZMK v0.3 the upstream corne shield ships two physical layouts
 * (5col + 6col) for ZMK Studio. We don't use Studio and Miryoku is built for
 * the 42-key (6col) mapping, so drop the 5col layout. This leaves a single
 * layout (6col), which avoids any runtime layout switching to the 36-key 5col
 * layout (that would silently drop the outer columns). The 6col layout stays
 * chosen by the upstream corne.dtsi.
 *
 * Note: deleting *all* physical layouts and selecting zmk,matrix-transform
 * directly does not build on the half shields in v0.3 (the keymap binds to a
 * physical layout), so we keep exactly one.
 */

/delete-node/ &foostan_corne_5col_layout;
